## Execution Flow Details

### Development Workflow
1. Developer accesses Dev Spaces workspace via browser
2. Git repository cloned into workspace
3. Ansible Navigator used to execute playbooks
4. EE container pulled from registry if needed
5. Playbook executed within isolated container

### Security Model
- All secrets managed through OpenShift secrets
- No credentials stored in workspaces
- EE containers run with minimal privileges
- Network access controlled by policies

### Execution Environment Features
- Pre-built with required collections
- Version-controlled and immutable
- Signed and security scanned
- Consistent across all environments

### Benefits
- Consistent execution environment
- No local dependency management
- Enhanced security isolation
- Scalable and reproducible
- Complete audit trail